3. Anti-spoofing Kalman filter

When a spoofing signal intrudes into the GPS receiver, the navigation solution result of the receiver will deviate from the normal value, resulting in large positioning error or gradually deviate from the real value. The position of the carrier will be misled by the wrong navigation results. In the GPS/RINS integrated navigation system, the results of RINS are free from external interference and have sufficient accuracy in a short time. Therefore, the positioning value of GPS receiver can be judged by using the results of RINS and the priori results in the Kalman filter of the integration. Based on this, an anti-spoofing integrated nav­ igation method is proposed in this paper.

