4.1. Parameter configuration of simulation
In order to verify the effectiveness of the proposed method, a 4-h simulation experiment is carried out.
According to the accuracy of the RINS in our laboratory, the pa­ rameters of the IMU are set as shown in Table 1 and the main errors set in the simulation are shown in Table 2 where σGPS is the radial position error of GPS.
In the simulation, the carrier starts from the place with longitude of 120◦ and latitude of 40◦. The carrier carries out various maneuvers, such as acceleration and deceleration, constant speed driving, uphill and downhill, turning, etc. The data of the RINS and GPS positioning data are generated during the process. The trajectory of the carrier in the simulation is as Fig. 3.
The carrier starts from the green point and reaches the red point through the blue route. The velocity of the carrier during the simulation is shown as Fig. 4.

