The anti-spoofing Kalman filter for the integration of GPS and RINS proposed in this paper can improve the accuracy and reliability of in­ tegrated navigation system without modifying GPS receiver. Simulation and vehicular experiment show the effectiveness of the proposed method. In the vehicular experiment, the positioning accuracy obtained by this method can reach 176 m under the influence of spoofed GPS with positioning error of 8800 m in more than 100 min. The proposed method is of great significance to ensure the right result of the GPS/RINS inte­ grated navigation in the environment where GPS may be spoofed. In this paper, the RINS is used to verify the effectiveness of the method, but this method can also be used for SINS. In the future, the method based on machine learning is considered to judge spoofing by using the data of RINS and GPS, so as to improve the universality of the detection method and the adaptability of the detection threshold.
